### [Genesis Chapter 36](../../../bib/kjv/gen036.htm#001.md)

[Genesis 36:1](../../../bib/kjv/gen036.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_001">gen 36:1</span></span>

Edom

Edom (called also "Seir,") ([Gen
32:3](../../../bib/kjv/gen032.htm#003).md); ([Gen
36:8](../../../bib/kjv/gen036.htm#008).md) is the name of the country lying
south of the ancient kingdom of Judah, and extending from the Dead Sea
to the Gulf of Akaba. It includes the ruins of Petra, and is bounded on
the north by Moab. Peopled by descendants of Esau ([Gen
36:1-9](../../../bib/kjv/gen036.htm#001).md). Edom has a remarkable
prominence in the prophetic word as (together with Moab) the scene of
the final destruction of Gentile world-power in the day of the Lord. See
"Armageddon"; ([Rev 16:14](../../../bib/kjv/rev016.htm#014).md); ([Rev
19:21](../../../bib/kjv/rev019.htm#021).md) and "Times of the Gentiles";
([Luk 21:24](../../../bib/kjv/luk021.htm#024).md); ([Rev
16:14](../../../bib/kjv/rev016.htm#014).md).

Compare ([Psa 137:7](../../../bib/kjv/psa137.htm#007).md); ([Oba
1:8-16](../../../bib/kjv/oba001.htm#008).md); ([Isa
34:1-8](../../../bib/kjv/isa034.htm#001).md); ([Isa
63:1-6](../../../bib/kjv/isa063.htm#001).md); ([Jer
49:14-22](../../../bib/kjv/jer049.htm#014).md); ([Eze
25:12-14](../../../bib/kjv/eze025.htm#012).md).

